  "1.0": "",
  "3.0": "",
  "2.0": "",
  "Debt-to-equity ratio = Total debt / Total equity = $200,000 / $100,000 = 2.0. This indicates relatively high leverage, meaning the business uses twice as much debt as owner equity.": "",
  "Excessive debt (overleveraging) is dangerous because:": "",
