  "What does 'concentration risk' mean in business?": "",
  "The risk of having too many business locations in one area": "",
  "The risk of employees losing focus during work": "",
  "The risk of having too much cash concentrated in one bank": "",
  "The risk that comes from depending too heavily on a single customer, product, supplier, or market": "",
  "Concentration risk arises when a business is overly dependent on a single source of revenue, customer, supplier, or market. If that single source is lost, the impact on the business is disproportionately large.": "",
  "What does 'debt-to-equity ratio' measure?": "",
  "The total amount of money a business earns": "",
  "The profit margin on each product sold": "",
  "The proportion of a company's financing that comes from debt compared to owner equity": "",
  "The cash flow available to pay dividends": "",
  "The debt-to-equity ratio (D/E) compares total liabilities (debt) to total shareholder equity. A higher ratio indicates more leverage and greater financial risk.": "",
